In order to calculate fractal parameters and volumetric densities of vacancies in collision cascades (ρ), we analyzed 3D distributions of ballistically-generated vacancies with an algorithm similar to that used by Heinisch and Singh5. First, for every vacancy in a cascade, we calculated31 the number of neighboring vacancies (N
v) whose coordinates lie within a sphere of radius R
c centered on that vacancy. After that, the target was divided into slices of equal widths (\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
