The bulk defect peak shift can be explained by the second contribution from the ρ-related damage formation efficiency that reflects the fraction of ballistic displacements that contribute to the creation of stable lattice damage rather than annihilate via DA processes. Regions characterized by larger ρ values (at depths larger than the R
pd; see Fig. 1) will exhibit more efficient damage buildup in irradiation regimes characterized by strong DA (which also includes 3C-SiC but at temperatures \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
